<TITLE> 3 bodies found at Turag river bank </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 27 (bdnews24.com) Police recovered three dead bodies from a residential project near Mohammadpur's Dhaka Park on Tuesday. The bodies were had been placed in a hole and levelled with sand at the Turag river bank near Chandrima Real Estate area. The bodies, which could not be identified immediately, were tied with ropes. Two of them were naked. Local people told bdnews24.com that a fisherman had informed the project workers on seeing a gathering of crows and dogs beside the river while fishing. Mahbub Hasan, OC of Mohammadpur Police Station, told bdnews24.com that the deaths might have taken place 4-5 days ago. Signs of the use of a sharp weapon was found on one body. The police officer said the men might have come from a different area and were buried naked to hide their identity. A lot of murders have taken place at Dhaka Park and its surrounding areas  with the river-side area well known as a high crime zone in Dhaka. bdnews24.
